# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DEPLOYMENT PRESET — SaaS / white-label client (a copy of the DECLICK DIGITAL
# preset with the brand parameterised). K-LMS is the product; each client gets
# their own brand by config alone — no code fork.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# To onboard a new client:
#   1. cp saas-client.env.example deploy/presets/<client>.env  (keep out of git)
#   2. Fill every <…> placeholder with the client's brand + domains.
#   3. Build web with these vars, deploy the server with the .env section, and
#      (optionally) build the native apps with the client's CAP_APP_ID.
# See ../../BRANDING.md for the full onboarding walkthrough.

# ===== Web / native build (VITE_* — baked at `npm -w web run build`) =====
VITE_API_URL=https://api.<client-domain>/api/v1
VITE_BRAND_NAME=<Client Platform Name>
VITE_BRAND_SHORT=<ShortName>
VITE_BRAND_OPERATOR=<Operating org or department>
VITE_BRAND_ISSUER=<Certifying entity>
VITE_BRAND_THEME=#RRGGBB
# Native bundle identifier (reverse-DNS of the client domain). PERMANENT.
CAP_APP_ID=<tld.client.app>

# ===== Server (.env — see deploy/.env.example for the full list) =====
CREDENTIAL_ISSUER_NAME=<Certifying entity>
CREDENTIAL_ISSUER_URL=https://<client-domain>
CORS_ORIGINS=https://app.<client-domain>,https://<client-domain>,capacitor://localhost,https://localhost
